data.content:
Yes — use `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>()`. In MSTest v3+ it returns the cast object, so you can combine the type check and assignment:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()
{
    var factory = new HandlerFactory();
    var result = factory.Create("email");

    var handler = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(result);
    Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
}
```

**Why this is better:**
- Fails with a clear message if the type is wrong (instead of an `InvalidCastException`)
- Eliminates the manual cast
- The generic overload returns the typed object, so you can keep asserting on it directly
